qas.question: Name the largest country in Southeast Asia.
Geologically what is Indonesia's region most active for?
What is the largest country in Asia?
What is the smallest archipelago in the world?
What country has the least volcanic activity in Southeast Asia?
What is the only mountain without glaciers in Souteast Asia?
What  is the second largest peak in Asia?

context: <a0_0><b2_0><b3_0><b4_0>Indonesia<b4_0/><b3_0/><b2_0/><a0_0/> is the largest country in Southeast Asia and it also the largest archipelago in the world by size (according to the CIA World Factbook). Geologically, the Indonesian Archipelago is one of the most <a1_0>volcanically active<a1_0/> regions in the world. Geological uplifts in the region have also produced some impressive mountains, culminating in <b5_0>Puncak Jaya<b5_0/> in Papua, Indonesia at 5,030 metres (16,500 feet), on the island of New Guinea; it is the only place where ice glaciers can be found in Southeast Asia. The second tallest peak is <b6_0>Mount Kinabalu<b6_0/> in Sabah, Malaysia on the island of Borneo with a height of 4,095 metres (13,435 feet). The highest mountain in Southeast Asia is Hkakabo Razi at 5,967 meters and can be found in northern Burma sharing the same range of its parent peak, Mount Everest.
